The article discusses the celebration of American Red Cross Month, which honors the humanitarian efforts of the American people. The American Red Cross has been helping prevent and alleviate human suffering for 140 years, with over 90 percent of its workforce consisting of volunteers. The article highlights the selfless acts of Americans during the challenges of the past year, including becoming new Red Cross volunteers, donating blood, and providing emergency assistance during natural disasters and the COVID-19 pandemic. It emphasizes the importance of coming together as a nation to support one another in times of crisis and encourages Americans to participate in acts of compassion. President Joseph R. Biden Jr. proclaims March 2021 as American Red Cross Month and urges citizens to observe the month by supporting service and relief organizations.